    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-06-28T19:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-06-28T19:18:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <head>492. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d492fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 792.551/6–2858. Confidential; Priority. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRH1">Bushner</persName>; cleared with the Department of
                        Defense and the Office of the Special Assistant for Mutual Security Affairs
                        in the Department of State; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                            >Robertson</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                            >CINCPAC</gloss> for POLAD.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-06-28T20:18:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1958—8:18 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3175. Department’s 3120.<note n="2" xml:id="d492fn2">
                        <ref target="#d490">Document 490</ref>.</note> Re <persName corresp="#p_TS1"
                        >Sarit</persName>’s request for comments to supplement written reply you
                    authorized provide following orally: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Secretary had hoped to see Field Marshal again before latter’s
                            departure and sincerely regretted this was not possible because
                                <persName corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> had to leave on short
                            notice.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Following points provided by Defense illustrate our active interest in
                            particular problems facing Thai armed services: <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>Re Army construction programs mentioned <persName
                                        corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> memo (<gloss
                                        target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. and discussed JUSMAG’s
                                        MA-7410<note n="3" xml:id="d492fn3">Not found.</note> End
                                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>), Defense Department has
                                    stated will give serious consideration Thai recommendations
                                    which meet <gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> criteria and are
                                    submitted through JUSMAG. Military industrial projects,
                                    including rebuild line for major assemblies and certain items in
                                    communications and medical and troop housing already
                                    programmed.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Defense Department hopes Congress will enact legislation
                                    authorizing loan of destroyer escort to Thailand. FY 1959
                                    program now under Congressional consideration includes request
                                    for funds to cover rehabilitation this vessel. Proposal to lend
                                    Thailand other vessels not requiring Congressional authorization
                                    is also under active consideration, provided funds are
                                    available.</item>
                                <pb facs="1071" n="1039" xml:id="pg_1039"/>
                                <label>C.</label>
                                <item>Assistance for further modernization Thai Air Force depends
                                    upon availability of funds and aircraft in FY 1959.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Re 2, suggest you determine in consultation Chief JUSMAG items requested in
                        <persName corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> memo which already in approved
                    FY 1958 program so you can enumerate for <persName corresp="#p_TS1"
                        >Sarit</persName>. May also be possible indicate some items included in
                    planned program FY 1959 subject availability funds. Should be made clear no
                    final approval such items has been received and can make no definite commitment
                    regarding them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
